    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550 E 1/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Italian Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ricci</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation<note n="6" xml:id="d103fn6">File
                            translation revised.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to my note of the
                    16th instant, I have, by order of my Government, the honor to forward herewith
                    to Your Excellency the agenda of the Conference of Genoa, approved at Cannes by
                    the Supreme Council at its forenoon session of January 11, 1922: <list>
                        <label>1)</label>
                        <item>Examination of methods for the putting into operation of the
                            principles contained in the resolutions approved at Cannes by the
                            Supreme Council on January 6, 1922;</item>
                        <pb facs="0509" n="389" xml:id="pg_389"/>
                        <label>2)</label>
                        <item>Establishing the peace of Europe on a firm basis;</item>
                        <label>3)</label>
                        <item>Conditions necessary to restore confidence without prejudice to the
                            existing treaties;</item>
                        <label>4)</label>
                        <item>Financial questions: <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Circulation;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Central banks and banks of issue;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Public finances with respect to the reconstruction
                                    work;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Exchanges;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">e</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Organization of public and private credit;</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>5)</label>
                        <item>Economic and commercial questions: <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Facilities and guarantees for the import and export
                                    trade;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Guarantees of law and legal practice for the resumption of
                                    commerce;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Protection of industrial, literary and artistic
                                    property;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Consular laws and regulations;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">e</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Admission and status of foreigners with respect to their
                                    engaging in business;</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">f</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Technical assistance in the work of industrial
                                    reconstruction.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                        <label>6)</label>
                        <item>Transportation.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">V. Rolandi Ricci</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
